Just wondering if you've signed some exclusivity contract with them for way too long......and, if you have maybe you also have an NDA restricting you from speaking openly and clearly on this matter.
I hope if that's the case that you're on the tail end of both things (contract & NDA).
You don't have to answer these questions, and I guess you may not even be (legally) able to, and that's fine.
Please don't feel criticised here. That's really really not my intention. I admire both you and the work you do very greatly, and I totally understand that sponsorship is necessary in order to continue to provide it. I just hope that you can find good sponsorship from a brand more aligned with the values that (I understand) you to represent. Putting out the good vibes for you, sister!
Meanwhile, keep being wonderful! xxx

Hello! In "the before time," I practiced yoga 3x/week at a hot yoga studio and was a mess if I went more than a few days in between. Then the pandemic hit, and I started doing yoga at home with the classes my studio live streamed. But, it just wasn't the same for so many reasons, and my practice frequency, duration, and intensity dropped--and dropped some more. I knew about YWA, but was really committed to using the videos from my studio with my familiar teachers. Well, they had to stop live streaming videos because they ran out of money and had to go dormant until after the pandemic passes. So, I turned to YWA and have really loved both Adriene's personal style and warmth as well as the ability to find a video to meet any and all of my random, "I wonder if she has one for ____" searches. The most recent: Yoga after a long trip. Bingo! Thanks, Adriene, for being there for all of us. I am a little doubtful I will be able to practice every single day of the 30-day journey, but I am committed to trying. I can and will do this! :) Happy 2021, all!! Let's do this! (Madison, WI)

So excited to be jumping into this next thirty day challenge. I've done them all, since the beginning, and have practiced them from different locations almost every year. This year, I'm tuning in from Baltimore, Maryland, from the house I grew up in, the only house I knew until I turned 18, moved away, and started adventuring. Now I'm circling back to my hometown, the house my mother has owned for thirty-six years, the house she will (if all goes according to plan) be selling at the end of this new year as she turns 70, retires, and moves back to HER hometown of Syracuse, New York. My last year in my old home. A perfect place to breathe. Thank you for helping me start my new years off right for so many years in a row, Adriene. I'm tuning in because of the deliciousness I've found in previous years: the love, the discoveries, the health. Ready to find what feels good with all of you beautiful souls! Happy 2021, everyone! Here's to a year of connection, integration, healing, and BREATH.

I, like many of you, am SO looking forward to this 30 day yoga journey. I have been virtually hangin with Adrienne since 2015, and though I’ve said it before I feel the need to say it again - thank you for this gift you give to all of us so freely and humbly.  It is not only the way you carefully craft each practice with modifications for every skill level or body type, or the way you gently remind us that “we’ve gotta bring the breath”. It is not only your charisma and warmth and humor that make it so easy to return to the mat (okay maybe not always easy, but once we’re there we remember why). It is not only your teachings on self love and compassion, which remind us to find love and pride in who we are right now, in a world that is so quick to tell us otherwise. It is not only the way you gracefully roll with Mis-saying or mis-steps, or groans from your “breathing bolster” Benji, reminding us that no one is perfect and that there is a humanness, a beauty in imperfection. It is also the community you have woven together, with people all over the world from all walks of life who all share the same desire and pull to practice together. This is perhaps the most beautiful thing you and your channel offer. In a time where in-person gathering  is unavailable, when so many are feeling isolated in a time where we need community most. Thank you for creating a safe, welcoming space for us all to gather virtually 🙏🏻 namaste to all and may 2021 bring more light, more peace, more love, more unity for all. ❤️

why are you here... what holds you here. these were so clear questions.

Yoga makes me happy, i'm here to (find a) flow and find stilness in my mind, or.. strive to accept it isn't. Im' here to break chains of thoughts that do no longer serve and to find inner peace when possible. I want to be me unapoli... can't spell the word. I want to acces the strength in me, that energy that's always there but for some reason often out of my reach.
AND I WANNA DO SOME COOL ASS YOGA POSES,... and maybe, just maybe i'll be in touch with my needs, and then improvise, find my flow <3

Reality: probably going to be angry for not beig able to follow or going to fast. Might get frustrated at you adriene, nothing personal. I'll probably do more effort than what's necessary (ty hard instead of easy). I'm very often going to ask myself if i'm doing it right, and question every inch² of my body. "is my back straight this way?" "is my head at the right angle?" "shoudln't i be doing this to achieve that?" "am i breathing deep enough?" "am i doing this pose right to get it's benefits?" "is my energy flowing when ..."

What holds me here?

There is something about yoga. When i move and follow that flow, it feels so liberating. I honestly don't get it. it's very very weird to me just because there is so much that i havent learnt yet, and that i don't not know. i just love connecting with myself. And i sometimes succeed when doing yoga. Yoga learns me so much about my mind and my own energy, i can use what i learn in yoga in other parts of my life.
My curiosity holds me here, my will to move forward and discover inner peace, happiness, the present. But honestly also expectations of succes. Sometimes yoga becomes a tool and that's weird, i'm going to try and find balance in that. I sometimes try to use yoga to change how i feel... but that's not really connecting with yourself.

Thank you Adriene for spreading this craft <3 i'm looking forward to the creaky floor, tha AYOO's, the allusions you're going to make, the references that i sometimes don't understand.
Happy new year, happy new challenges and chances, best of luck 🙏❤️

Just did a yoga session and a flash of insight came up inside of me which was quite profound. It said something that the magic of this community isn't necessarily Adrienne herself as a separate individual and that she's some sort of authority in relation to her students, but the magic comes from the whole community and everyone's relationship to the practice.

I find that in fitness and wellness circles in general, there is a tendency that you want to find a certain person to be inspired by, some guru to "believe in" or some authority who you should be like. In this community, there is a totally different vibe. Here, everyone is themselves their most important guru and their biggest inspiration. Adrienne is more an intention-setter and a messenger of these techniques, but the true difference comes from every single individual who is practicing.

It brought me a great sense of enthusiasm and hope for the future and what's possible if people get this.

Happy new year everyone!

I am excited for this new fresh start. I am having wrist issues, so I am not sure if I'll be able to do all of it though 😳 I always end up skpping a few days in challenges like this. How is with me on that? I will return to this post if/when that happens and I'm going to be here to encourage anyone on the same train to continue the next day 💜 We are not competing, we are being nice to ourselves and this is a journey 🎆

Yes indeed to wrist issues! I have no left hand, and I got around that with yoga blocks, but I have a lot of wrist problems in my right wrist as it's my only one. I got to 99 days straight of yoga last year and absolutely loved it so much, but was stopped by a surprise urgent Thyroidectomy! Now my wrist problems are almost completely stopping me from using my hand at all during yoga. Do you use anything to ease your wrists? I have a yoga glove with a silicone wedge and without that I wouldn't ever have been able to use my wrist during yoga. They're amazing and well worth it. It's hard sometimes not being able to complete days in these challenges, or just normally when practising with any video, but I try and still show up, and mix it up with some hands-free stuff or use forearms where possible and join back in when the bit that I can't do has finished. It's not competing no, and even just rolling out our mat or whatever and taking five minutes to sit and breathe is enough. And if we miss a day, or a week, well so what?! The intention is there, and that's more than enough 💚
